def: In a handfast or publicly pledged manner. [Obs.] Holinshed.
An alkaloid, , prepared from codeine. In its effects itresembles apomorphine.
In French usage, a dish served at the beginning of dinner togive zest to the appetite; in English usage, a side dish, served witha joint, or between the courses, as a cutlet, scalloped oysters, etc.

Any one of numerous species of small rodents belonging to thegenus Mus and various related genera of the family Murid√¶. The commonhouse mouse (Mus musculus) is found in nearly all countries. TheAmerican white-footed, or deer, mouse (Hesperomys leucopus) sometimeslives in houses. See Dormouse, Meadow mouse, under Meadow, andHarvest mouse, under Harvest.
Naked-fruited, the fruit either smooth or not adherent to theperianth. Gray.
Such as can be, or is liable to be, combated; as, combatablefoes, evils, or arguments.
Having its substance arranged in strata, or layers; as,stratified rock.
To commove; to disturb; to stir up. [R.]Society being more or less commoted and made uncomfortable.Hawthorne.

A device utilized in the making of a loud-speaking telephone,depending on the fact that the friction between a metallic point anda moving cylinder of moistened chalk, or a moving slip of paper, onwhich it rests is diminished by the passage of a current between thepoint and the moving surface. -- Mo`to*graph"ic (#), a.
The act of burning different things together. [Obs.]
